text: Crewe is a crater approximately 3 km in diameter lying situated within the Margaritifer Sinus quadrangle (MC-19) region of the planet Mars, located at 25° South, 10° West. The crater was named after the town of Crewe, Cheshire, England. ==External links== *Roving Mouse Mars Atlas feature index Category:Impact craters on Mars Category:Margaritifer Sinus quadrangle
